{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"502b31e6-d565-4e96-b8a2-7fb465f08ce1","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so simply removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is sufficient.\n2. **Test execution changes** — use `dotnet test` as before, but the underlying runner is now Microsoft.Testing.Platform. You can also run the test executable directly.\n3. **CLI differences** — some VSTest CLI options (e.g., `--filter`) work the same, but platform-specific options use `--` syntax (e.g., `dotnet test -- --filter \"Name=MyTest\"`).\n4. **Remove any VSTest-specific runsettings** that aren't compatible, and migrate them to the new platform configuration if needed.\n5. **Extensions** — if you use VSTest adapters/extensions, verify they have Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cae7271d-c33c-4150-88d9-b90f6728e97c","outputTokens":391,"requestId":"0423:C1158:1F08253:22D8070:69E81A52"},"id":"05ef2a99-8ab9-4fbc-81ea-1f76b2d635ad","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:25.161Z","parentId":"78cac108-c8bc-4f5d-ad5a-e98d38f8fdc6"}
